                    %h2.section-title CORNERBACK BASICS FUNDAMENTALS
                    %h6 'DB Fundamentals'
                    %h3 Weeks 1-6
                    %h5 PHASE I: GET IN SHAPE, LEARN THE DRILLS.
                    %table.breakdown
                      %tr
                        %th WEEK
                        %th SUMMARY
                        %th SPEED
                        %th FOOTWORK
                        %th STRENGTH
                      %tr
                        %td 1
                        %td
                          %h3 'The Warm-Up'
                          %p Light workout week designed to stretch the body, stimulate muscular adaptation and establish form and technique in speed, footwork  agility drills. Focus on learning the drills. Speed training will be extremely light.
                        %td
                          2x1 Mile
                          = succeed "Strides" do
                            %br/
                        %td
                          50yd LD,
                          = succeed "Box" do
                            %br/
                        %td
                          AA
                          = succeed "18RM" do
                            %br/
                      %tr
                        %td 2
                        %td
                          %h3 'Oiling the Gears'
                          %p Moderate increases in training volume this week. Speed training will continue to be light. Footwork  agility training will increase in distance, continue to focus on mastering the drills. For weights, push through soreness, increase the weight, decrease rest.
                        %td
                          2x1 mile
                          = succeed "Strides" do
                            %br/
                        %td
                          75yd LD,
                          = succeed "Box" do
                            %br/
                        %td
                          AA
                          = succeed "16RM" do
                            %br/
                      %tr
                        %td 3
                        %td
                          %h3 'Ready for Action'
                          %p All movements should feel more natural. You will push hard this week in every area: a first taste of speed work with active recovery sprints @ 90%, increased distance and volume for footwork and agility drills, as well as a "heavier" strength training week to finish off your first 3 week micro-cycle.
                        %td
                          2x1 mile
                          = succeed "Sprints" do
                            %br/
                        %td
                          100yd LD,
                          = succeed "Box" do
                            %br/
                        %td
                          AA
                          = succeed "14RM" do
                            %br/
                      %tr
                        %td 4
                        %td
                          %h3 'Training Wheels Off'
                          %p
                            You should feel noticeable improvements in your strength, body mechanics, and endurance. It's go time! You'll be training For explosive start and short burst speed. Focus on your technique and having smooth transitions in your DB drills.
                          %p
                            Strength training will focus on building muscle for the next 3-4 weeks. Make sure your 12RM is a 12RM. Also make sure you EAT enough, DRINK enough WATER, and get enough protein to support your muscle growth.
                        %td 20yd Burst 10X, Stadiums 5X
                        %td
                          DB Drills 2X,
                          %br/
                          CA Drills 4X
                        %td MH 12RM
                      %tr
                        %td 5
                        %td
                          %h3 'Turn up the Volume'
                          %p Fight fatigue and concentrate on training with an impeccable sense of focus, detail and quality. Challenge yourself to increase your training intensity on speed workouts, footwork drills, and strength training sessions.
                        %td 20yd Burst 12X, Stadiums 6X
                        %td
                          DB Drills 2X,
                          %br/
                          CA Drills 6X
                        %td MH 10RM
                      %tr
                        %td 6
                        %td
                          %h3 'No Technique Leaks'
                          %p This is the end of Phase 1. You're cornerback and sprint technique should feel a bit more natural. Continue to focus on perfecting each rep. If you mess up, start over again. Shutdown cornerbacks DO NOT PRACTICE BAD HABITS.
                        %td 20yd Burst 14X, Stadiums 7X
                        %td
                          DB Drills 2X,
                          %br/
                          CA Drills 8X
                        %td MH 8RM
          
